<Class name="CM_ISOType" id="a8a1cb89-834d-46d0-a65d-94ef02c92cbc">
    <superclass name="CM_Object"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>ISOType entries in the ISO types table.
We only actually hold details on the 3rd and 4th digits of the ISO type, the 1st 2 are
coded into the method that works over the ISOTypeTable class. This uses methods to
determine the height, and length, then comes to here for the rest of the data (attributes)
This is a SYSTEM TABLE, no user alterations may be made.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="terminal"/>
